The paper is about reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. Specifically, it focuses on temporal-difference learning, which is a type of online learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the application of these methods to robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, it mentions the use of linear function approximation (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) for feature representation.
